  Demo.java
public class Demo {
    public void greet() {
        System.out.println("Hello from Demo!");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Demo d = new Demo();
        d.greet();
    }
}

Compile the class
javac Demo.java

Decompile the .class file
You can use popular tools:

JD-GUI (GUI tool)

Download from: http://java-decompiler.github.io/

Open Demo.class file, it shows the source code.

CFR (Command Line)

Download from: https://www.benf.org/other/cfr/

Run:

java -jar cfr.jar Demo.class

Sample Decompiled Output
public class Demo {
    public Demo() {
    }

    public void greet() {
        System.out.println("Hello from Demo!");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Demo d = new Demo();
        d.greet();
    }
}


